## 4. Icons & Splash Screens

### Icon Requirements

Design your source icon at **1024×1024px** (SVG preferred) and generate all sizes from it.

| Purpose | Size | Format | Notes |
|:---|:---|:---|:---|
| **Favicon** | 32×32 | `.ico` or `.png` | Legacy browser tab icon |
| **Apple Touch Icon** | 180×180 | `.png` | iOS home screen. No rounded corners — iOS adds them. |
| **PWA Standard** | 192×192 | `.png` | Required for Chrome/Android installability |
| **PWA High-Res** | 512×512 | `.png` | Used for splash screens and high-DPI displays |
| **Maskable** | 512×512 | `.png` | Android adaptive icons. Keep content within inner 80%. |

### Maskable Icons — The Safe Zone

```
┌─────────────────────────┐
│                         │  ← Outer 20% — may be cropped
│   ┌─────────────────┐   │
│   │                 │   │
│   │   SAFE ZONE     │   │  ← Inner 80% — all content here
│   │   (Your Logo)   │   │
│   │                 │   │
│   └─────────────────┘   │
│                         │
└─────────────────────────┘
```

> [!WARNING]
> Maskable icons MUST have an **opaque background** (no transparency). Android will apply its own shape mask (circle, squircle, etc.) and a transparent icon will render with ugly artifacts.

### Splash Screens

| Platform | How It Works |
|:---|:---|
| **Android (Chrome)** | Automatically generated from manifest `name`, `background_color`, and 512px `icon`. No custom image needed. |
| **iOS (Safari)** | Does **NOT** use the manifest. Requires custom `<link rel="apple-touch-startup-image">` meta tags in the HTML `<head>` for each screen size, or use a library like `pwacompat` to automate generation. |

