## 7. Native-Like UX Patterns

The difference between "website in a standalone window" and "native-like app" comes down to UX details.

### Navigation & Transitions

| Pattern | Implementation |
|:---|:---|
| **View Transitions API** | Use `document.startViewTransition()` for seamless cross-fade or shared-element transitions between pages |
| **SPA Architecture** | Use React/Vue/Angular to avoid full page reloads. Keep navigation state in memory. |
| **Bottom Navigation** | Place primary nav at the bottom of the screen (thumb zone). This is the #1 native-like pattern. |
| **Pull-to-Refresh** | Implement custom pull-to-refresh with smooth spring animation (CSS `overscroll-behavior` to disable browser's default) |
| **Swipe Gestures** | Use Pointer Events (`pointerdown`, `pointermove`, `pointerup`) for custom swipe navigation |

### Animation Best Practices

| Do | Don't |
|:---|:---|
| Animate `transform` and `opacity` (GPU-accelerated) | Animate `width`, `height`, `top`, `left` (triggers layout reflow) |
| Use physics-based easing (spring curves) | Use linear or generic `ease` timing functions |
| Keep animations under 300ms for interactions | Use animations > 500ms that feel sluggish |
| Use `will-change` sparingly on elements that will animate | Apply `will-change` to everything (wastes GPU memory) |
| Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` user preference | Force animations on users who've opted out |

```css
/* Respect user motion preferences */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *, *::before, *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

### Typography & Visual Fidelity

- Use `font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;` to match the device's native font
- Or use a high-quality web font (Inter, Plus Jakarta Sans) loaded via `font-display: swap`
- Use `-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased` and `-moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale` for crisp text

### Touch & Interaction

- **Touch targets**: Minimum 44×44 CSS pixels (Apple HIG) / 48×48dp (Material Design)
- **Disable text selection on UI elements**: `user-select: none` on buttons and nav
- **Disable long-press context menu on interactive elements**: `-webkit-touch-callout: none`
- **Disable tap highlight**: `-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent` (then add your own feedback)
- **Skeleton screens**: Use animated skeleton loaders instead of spinners during data fetches

### Overscroll Behavior

```css
/* Prevent the "bounce" / "pull-to-navigate" behavior */
html, body {
  overscroll-behavior: none;
}

/* Allow only vertical overscroll (for custom pull-to-refresh) */
.scrollable-content {
  overscroll-behavior-y: contain;
}
```

