## 8. Push Notifications

### Architecture

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant App
    participant SW as Service Worker
    participant Push as Push Service (FCM/APNs)
    participant Server

    User->>App: Clicks "Enable Notifications"
    App->>User: Browser permission prompt
    User->>App: Grants permission
    App->>SW: PushManager.subscribe({ applicationServerKey: VAPID_PUBLIC })
    SW->>Push: Registers subscription
    Push->>App: Returns PushSubscription (endpoint + keys)
    App->>Server: Sends PushSubscription to backend
    Note right of Server: Stores subscription in DB

    Server->>Push: Sends push message (signed with VAPID_PRIVATE)
    Push->>SW: Delivers push event
    SW->>User: Shows notification
    User->>App: Clicks notification → deep link opens
```

### Best Practices

| Practice | Why |
|:---|:---|
| **Never request permission on page load** | Users haven't built trust yet. ~60% deny on first visit. |
| **Use a "soft prompt" first** | Show a custom UI explaining *why* notifications are valuable, with "Enable" / "Not Now" |
| **Trigger after engagement** | Ask after the user completes a key action (e.g., saves a favorite, completes onboarding) |
| **Personalize content** | Send relevant, targeted notifications — not generic blasts |
| **Include a clear CTA** | Every notification should have one clear action and deep-link to relevant content |
| **Offer granular control** | Let users choose notification categories (e.g., "Price alerts" vs "Marketing") |
| **Limit frequency** | 1–3 notifications per day maximum. Respect user attention. |

### iOS Push Notification Requirements (iOS 16.4+)
- The PWA **must** be installed to the home screen (push doesn't work in browser tabs)
- Permission must be requested via a **user gesture** (button click)
- VAPID authentication is required on the backend
- Each push event **must** display a visible notification

> [!CAUTION]
> **Never expose your VAPID private key** in client-side code. Store it in server environment variables only.

