## 9. Offline Data & Background Sync

### Architecture Pattern

```mermaid
graph TB
    A[User Action<br>e.g. Submit Form] --> B{Online?}
    B -->|Yes| C[Send to Server]
    B -->|No| D[Save to IndexedDB<br>Outbox Queue]
    D --> E[Register Background Sync]
    E -->|Connectivity Restored| F[Service Worker<br>sync Event Fires]
    F --> G[Read from IndexedDB Outbox]
    G --> H[Send to Server]
    H -->|Success| I[Remove from Outbox]
    H -->|Failure| J[Retry with<br>Exponential Backoff]
    C --> K[Success Response]
```

### Key Technologies

| Technology | Purpose | Browser Support |
|:---|:---|:---|
| **IndexedDB** | Persistent, structured local storage (large datasets) | All modern browsers ✅ |
| **Cache API** | Store HTTP request/response pairs for offline access | All modern browsers ✅ |
| **Background Sync** | Defer network requests until connectivity | Chromium only (Chrome, Edge) ⚠️ |
| **Periodic Background Sync** | Fetch fresh data on a schedule (e.g., news) | Chromium only, browser-controlled frequency ⚠️ |

### Fallback for Non-Chromium (Safari/Firefox)

```javascript
// When Background Sync isn't available, fall back to online event
if ('serviceWorker' in navigator && 'SyncManager' in window) {
  // Use Background Sync
  registration.sync.register('outbox-sync');
} else {
  // Fallback: listen for online event
  window.addEventListener('online', () => {
    processOutboxQueue();
  });
}
```

> [!TIP]
> Use Workbox's `workbox-background-sync` module — it handles the IndexedDB queue, retry logic, and expiration automatically with just a few lines of configuration.

### User Feedback

Always communicate offline state to the user:
- Show an **offline indicator** banner when connectivity drops
- Mark pending items with a "Syncing..." or "Pending" badge
- Confirm when items have been successfully synced

