## 11. Performance & Core Web Vitals

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The Lighthouse PWA audit category has been **deprecated**. Performance validation now focuses on Core Web Vitals and the Chrome DevTools Application panel.

### Core Web Vitals Targets

| Metric | Target | What It Measures |
|:---|:---|:---|
| **LCP** (Largest Contentful Paint) | ≤ 2.5s | How fast the main content loads |
| **INP** (Interaction to Next Paint) | ≤ 200ms | How quickly the app responds to user input |
| **CLS** (Cumulative Layout Shift) | ≤ 0.1 | Visual stability — elements shouldn't jump around |

### Performance Optimization Checklist

- [ ] **Code split** aggressively — only load JS needed for the current route
- [ ] **Lazy load** images and below-the-fold components
- [ ] **Use modern image formats** (WebP/AVIF) with `<picture>` fallbacks
- [ ] **Precache the app shell** via service worker
- [ ] **Inline critical CSS** or use `<link rel="preload">` for render-blocking resources
- [ ] **Set `font-display: swap`** to avoid invisible text during font loading
- [ ] **Implement skeleton screens** for perceived performance
- [ ] **Minimize third-party scripts** — each one is a performance tax
- [ ] **Use `<link rel="preconnect">` and `<link rel="dns-prefetch">`** for external origins

