## 12. Security

### Security Checklist

| Layer | Requirement |
|:---|:---|
| **HTTPS** | Mandatory. Service workers won't register without it. |
| **HSTS** | Enable `Strict-Transport-Security` with `includeSubDomains` and `preload` |
| **CSP** | Strict Content Security Policy. Avoid `'unsafe-inline'` and `'unsafe-eval'`. Use nonces or hashes. |
| **SW Scope** | Limit service worker scope to the narrowest necessary path |
| **Cache Hygiene** | Never store auth tokens or PII in the Cache API |
| **SRI** | Use Subresource Integrity hashes for third-party scripts |
| **Input Sanitization** | Sanitize all data handled by the service worker |
| **SW File Caching** | Serve `service-worker.js` with `Cache-Control: no-cache` to ensure prompt updates |
| **Mixed Content** | Use `upgrade-insecure-requests` CSP directive to catch all mixed content |

> [!CAUTION]
> Service workers can intercept **all** network traffic within their scope. A compromised service worker is a full man-in-the-middle attack. Always validate and sanitize.

